rComments: easy class. Open book for midterm and final. You can bring whatever you want in the midterm and final. By the way, if you didn't do well in the midterm, the weight of midterm will transfer to final when you get high mark in the final. Trust me, choose this course, you never regret.
Really monotone speech with the occasional joke. Homework is plentiful but easy. However, tests are much harder.

This course is cross listed as SYS5120 (graduated systems science course) and is eaaaaaaasy if you are a math student.  Typically, the MAT students do well and the SYS students do not-so-well, so the grades are curved up.  He is a very nice marker as well, tries to give as many part marks as possible and gives bonus problems.

assigs were hard, midterm was hard i thought,, but final was very eassyyy,, average on final was like 83% and final grade avg was at least 7.5, just stick with this class,,the final was very fair (92% applied, 8% theory),and gives a previous final to study,and a bonus assig to boost up your midterm grade, dont be "transient",stay in this class haha

Poses difficult exam/assignment questions, but marks forgivingly. Answers questions in an almost riddle-like format to point you in the right direction, yet not hand the answer on a silver platter. A good guy, and a good prof.
Math students:  don't bother with this class.  It is for systems engineers and is bor-ring.  (Not to mention hard.)
